    "backgrounds": [
      {
        "slug": "sheriff",
        "label": "Sheriff",
        "description": "You keep order in Stonetop and protect it from outside threats. It might not be anything official, but everyone knows you've got a cool head and the weight to back up your words.\n\nWhen you **_bark an order or warning_**, roll +CHA: **on a 7+**, they must choose 1:\n\n- do what you say\n- dig in/take cover/flee or\n- attack you\n **_On a 10+_**, you can sense which one they're about to do and act first if you like; gain advantage if you do."
      },
      {
        "slug": "blood-soaked-past",
        "label": "Blood-Soaked Past",
        "description": "You left behind a life of violence and a name mothers used to scare their children. For whatever reason, the people of Stonetop took you (back?) in and treat you like one of their own.\n\nWhen you **_Persuade using violence or threats against someone who knows your black reputation_**, you can roll +STR instead of +CHA. Also, if you take the **Formidable** move, you can choose to roll +CON instead of +CHA.\n\nWhen you **_fight to kill without mercy or hesitation_**, you deal +1d4 damage."
      },
      {
        "slug": "storm-marked",
        "label": "Storm-Marked",
        "description": "You've been touched by Tor (Rain-maker, Thunderhead, Slayer-of-Beasts!) and bear runic markings similar to those etched into the Stone. When did the marks manifest? Are they a symbol of your strength, speed, and courage? Or their source?\n\nYou start with the **Storm Markings** major arcanum. Mark one of the boxes on the front of the Storm Markings sheet, and describe here the time you were struck by lightning and walked away unharmed."
      }
    ],
